ns0:DescribedValueSet.ns0:Purpose: (Clinical Focus: This value set contains concepts that represent a persistent or ongoing condition or diagnosis that may render the patient unable to provide reliable responses to the screening (e.g. comatose, confused, mentally retarded, altered mental status, altered level of consciousness).),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use Quality Data Model (QDM) category related to Diagnosis. The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have an ongoing or persistent diagnosis of cognitive impairment such as dementia.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes only relevant concepts associated with codes identifying any cognitive disorder that may render the patient unable to provide reliable responses (e.g. dementia). This is a grouping of ICD-10-CM and SNOMED CT codes.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that pertain to temporary cognitive impairment due to acute substance use (e.g. overdose or acute intoxication).)
